    {
      "type": "contrast_example",
      "content": "In Poem 2, notice the very last word: 悲しき (kanashiki). \n- Standard ending (Shuushikei): 悲し (kanashi) = 'is sad'.\n- Rentaikei ending: 悲しき (kanashiki).\n\nBecause the poet used **時ぞ (toki zo)**, the sentence is 'forced' to end in **悲しき**. This creates a logical link: 'It is at this *time* (ぞ) ... that autumn *is sad* (き)'. Without 'zo', the poem would simply end in 'kanashi'."
    },
